</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[227,1274,1244,1270]" box="[227,1274,1244,1270]" pageId="28" pageNumber="95">
From the Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[420,537,1244,1270]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Trilobitoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="28" pageNumber="95" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="peculiaris">
<emphasis box="[420,537,1244,1270]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="95">peculiaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, meaning ‘peculiar’ and referring to the unusual conch shape.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
