<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="96" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="29.[227,372,755,781]" box="[227,372,755,781]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,372,755,781]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="29" pageNumber="96" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,372,755,781]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[227,1436,802,969]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">
<typeStatus box="[227,336,802,828]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">Holotype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30477 is a phragmocone fragment with almost half a whorl length (
<figureCitation box="[1220,1330,802,828]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="28.[227,270,1999,2025]" captionTargetBox="[422,1239,1578,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-154@28.[415,1248,1570,1956]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Fig. 23. Trilobitoceras peculiaris sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.)." pageId="29" pageNumber="96">Fig. 23A</figureCitation>
). It has a depressed whorl profile (ww/wh= 1.63) with a broadly rounded venter characterised by two deep and wide ventral grooves. The flanks are almost parallel in their middle and the umbilical wall is almost flat (
<figureCitation box="[235,347,908,934]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="29.[227,270,1756,1782]" captionTargetBox="[258,1405,1431,1711]" captionTargetId="figure-303@29.[258,1405,1431,1711]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Fig. 24. Trilobitoceras peculiaris sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30477 (dorsal portion reconstructed). B. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30477, at ww =13.6 mm, wh =7.7 mm. C. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30478. D. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30478, at ww =13.6 mm, wh =7.9 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm." pageId="29" pageNumber="96">Fig. 24A</figureCitation>
). The suture line, whose course is determined by the shape of the whorl profile, has a very wide external lobe in which a low, broadly rounded median saddle rises (
<figureCitation box="[1083,1191,943,969]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="29.[227,270,1756,1782]" captionTargetBox="[258,1405,1431,1711]" captionTargetId="figure-303@29.[258,1405,1431,1711]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Fig. 24. Trilobitoceras peculiaris sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30477 (dorsal portion reconstructed). B. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30477, at ww =13.6 mm, wh =7.7 mm. C. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30478. D. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30478, at ww =13.6 mm, wh =7.9 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm." pageId="29" pageNumber="96">Fig. 24B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[227,1438,1008,1140]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">
<typeStatus box="[227,330,1009,1035]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">Paratype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30478 is a fragment consisting of only two chambers of the phragmocone (
<figureCitation box="[1314,1424,1008,1034]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="28.[227,270,1999,2025]" captionTargetBox="[422,1239,1578,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-154@28.[415,1248,1570,1956]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Fig. 23. Trilobitoceras peculiaris sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.)." pageId="29" pageNumber="96">Fig. 23B</figureCitation>
). The conch geometry is very similar to the 
<typeStatus box="[740,846,1043,1069]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">holotype</typeStatus>
, although the ww/wh ratio is slightly higher with a value of 1.72. (
<figureCitation box="[432,538,1079,1105]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="29.[227,270,1756,1782]" captionTargetBox="[258,1405,1431,1711]" captionTargetId="figure-303@29.[258,1405,1431,1711]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Fig. 24. Trilobitoceras peculiaris sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30477 (dorsal portion reconstructed). B. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30477, at ww =13.6 mm, wh =7.7 mm. C. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30478. D. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30478, at ww =13.6 mm, wh =7.9 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm." pageId="29" pageNumber="96">Fig. 24C</figureCitation>
) The suture line is also similar to the 
<typeStatus box="[992,1098,1079,1105]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">holotype</typeStatus>
; however, the specimen also shows the rather narrow, rounded V-shaped internal lobe (
<figureCitation box="[907,1017,1114,1140]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="29.[227,270,1756,1782]" captionTargetBox="[258,1405,1431,1711]" captionTargetId="figure-303@29.[258,1405,1431,1711]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Fig. 24. Trilobitoceras peculiaris sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30477 (dorsal portion reconstructed). B. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30477, at ww =13.6 mm, wh =7.7 mm. C. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30478. D. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30478, at ww =13.6 mm, wh =7.9 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm." pageId="29" pageNumber="96">Fig. 24D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="97" pageId="29" pageNumber="96" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[227,341,1179,1205]" box="[227,341,1179,1205]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,341,1179,1205]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="29" pageNumber="96" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,341,1179,1205]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[227,1437,1226,1323]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[227,518,1226,1252]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Trilobitoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="29" pageNumber="96" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="peculiaris" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[227,518,1226,1252]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">Trilobitoceras peculiaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[526,703,1226,1252]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has a very similar conch morphology like 
<taxonomicName box="[1207,1383,1226,1252]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Trilobitoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="29" pageNumber="96" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="planidorsale">
<emphasis box="[1207,1383,1226,1252]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">T. planidorsale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in the course of the suture line: 
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[688,835,1261,1287]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Trilobitoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="29" pageNumber="96" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="peculiaris" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[688,835,1261,1287]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">T. peculiaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[843,1021,1262,1288]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
possesses a mid-ventral saddle but 
<taxonomicName box="[228,404,1296,1322]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Trilobitoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="29" pageNumber="96" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="planidorsale">
<emphasis box="[228,404,1296,1322]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">T. planidorsale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses a mid-ventral lobe.
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="29" pageNumber="96" startId="29.[227,270,1756,1782]" targetBox="[258,1405,1431,1711]" targetPageId="29">
<paragraph blockId="29.[224,1437,1756,1888]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,318,1756,1782]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">Fig. 24.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[323,611,1756,1782]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Trilobitoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="29" pageNumber="96" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="peculiaris" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[323,611,1756,1782]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">Trilobitoceras peculiaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[617,706,1756,1782]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from Oued Temertasset (both Korn 
<emphasis box="[1119,1170,1756,1782]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">et al</emphasis>
. 2002 Coll.). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1326,1347,1756,1782]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">A</emphasis>
. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30477 (dorsal portion reconstructed). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[969,989,1791,1817]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">B</emphasis>
. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30477, at ww =13.6 mm, wh =7.7 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[607,628,1826,1852]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">C</emphasis>
. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30478. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1127,1148,1826,1852]" pageId="29" pageNumber="96">D</emphasis>
. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30478, at ww =13.6 mm, wh =7.9 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
